  "local_port": 48156,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you file a complain against an online shopping website in consumer court?",
  "response": "Filing a complaint against an online shopping website in consumer court involves several steps. Here's a general guide you can follow:\n\n### 1. **Gather Evidence**\n   - **Documentation**: Collect all relevant documents, including receipts, order confirmations, emails with customer service, and any other communication you had with the online retailer.\n   - **Screenshots**: Take screenshots of the product listing, any misleading information, and the issues you faced.\n\n### 2. **Contact Customer Support**\n   - Before escalating to consumer court, try to resolve the issue directly with the online shopping website. Contact their customer support, provide them with the facts, and see if they can remedy your complaint.\n\n### 3. **Draft a Formal Complaint**\n   If your issue is unresolved, prepare a formal complaint. Your complaint should include:\n   - Your name and contact details.\n   - Details of the online shopping website (name, address).\n   - A clear description of the issue (what happened, when it happened).\n   - Any attempts you made to resolve the issue directly with the company.\n   - Specific remedies you are seeking (refund, exchange, etc.).\n\n### 4. **Determine the Appropriate Forum**\n   - **Consumer Forum**: Identify the right consumer forum based on the value of your complaint:\n     - **District Consumer Forum**: For claims up to a specified amount (typically up to INR 20 lakhs in India).\n     - **State Consumer Forum**: For claims above that limit.\n     - **National Consumer Redressal Commission (NCDRC)**: For claims above a certain amount (typically over INR 1 crore in India).\n\n### 5. **Filing the Complaint**\n   - **Format**: Write your complaint in a format that is accepted by the consumer court. This often includes a title, introduction, body, and conclusion.\n   - **Application Fees**: Pay any required fees for filing the complaint. The fees vary depending on the value of your claim.\n   - **Submission**: Submit your complaint to the appropriate consumer forum either online (if they have an online filing system) or in person.\n\n### 6. **Await the Hearing**\n   - Once your complaint is filed, the consumer court will send you a notice regarding the hearing date.\n   - Be prepared to present your case during the hearing. Bring all your evidence and documentation.\n\n### 7. **Follow Up**\n   - After the hearing, wait for the judgment from the court. The consumer forum will inform you of their decision.\n\n### 8. **Compliance**\n   - If the judgment is in your favor, ensure that the online shopping website complies with the order.\n\n### Tips:\n- Make sure to keep copies of all documents and correspondence.\n- Be clear and concise in your complaint.\n- Seek legal advice if necessary, especially for more complicated cases.\n\n### Important:\nProcedures may vary based on your country, region, or even specific forums, so check local consumer protection laws for the most accurate guidance.",
